This paper deals with the problem of single-image depth estimation using neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed approach involves using surface normal annotations to train the network, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions experiments on NYU Depth, which is a popular dataset for computer graphics (cs.GR) and robotics (cs.RO) research.
